\cf4 To cement what we've been learning, let's look at a group of variables relating to things that we might loosely think of as risky behaviour-- smoking, drinking alcohol, using marijuana or had drugs, and early sex. We'll find that these things tend to go together and that people who've tried one are more likely to try another. We'll only look at people aged between 20 and 59, because several of these variables have only been recorded for these age groups. Let's start with regular marijuana use as our outcome variable and cigarette smoking as the predictor variable. For regular marijuana, participants were asked whether they had at some point used marijuana at least once a month for a year.\
