\cf4 Approximately 25% of respondents said "Yes" to the Regular Marijuana question, while about 42% said they'd smoked more than 100 cigarettes in their lifetime. We'll refer to those who said "Yes" to the Smoked 100 question as smokers and the "Nos" as non-smokers. Here, we've coloured the smoking plot by Smoke100n. From now on, smokers will be brown and non-smokers green. We're now looking at the relationship between Regular Marijuana (as the outcome variable), and Smoke100, (the predictive variable), as separate graphs and as side-by-side bar charts. It's very clear that the cigarette smokers are much more likely to say "Yes" to the Marijuana question than the non-smokers-- (more than 40% for smokers versus less than 10% for non-smokers).\
