\cf4 The side-by-side bars, (the right hand plot), make it much easier to gauge visually how much more likely the smokers, (brown), are to say "Yes" to the Marijuana question than the non-smokers, (green). The brown "Yes" bar looks more than four times as high as the green "Yes" bar. So the cigarette smokers are more than four times as likely to say "Yes" to having used marijuana regularly, than the non-smokers. Our next question is, "Does this pattern change with age?" The pattern of smokers being much more likely to say "Yes" to the Regular Marijuana question is remarkably consistent across all of the age groups. The brown smokers "Yes" bars are always much taller than the green non-smokers "Yes" bars.\
